    "comment": "Rationale: Immunofluorescence of rat neuromuscular junctions shows that CDK5 is colocalized with postsynaptic acetylcholine receptors.\n\n9/2/2018 Pim\n- The data in Fig.2 do not resolve the postsynapse from other synaptic compartments. In order to reach this conclusion the authors integrate gene expression and functional data on CDK5 regulating nAChR expression in myotubes.. Experimental description: Methods:\nImmunohistochemical analysis.\nThe rat muscle sections (10 μm) were collected from various developmental stages and after nerve injury as previously described",
